sentences: Irina Lankova (born September 11, 1977, in Michurinsk, Russia) is an international concert pianist.
After her successful Wigmore Hall debut in 2008, Irina Lankova was invited to join the worldwide piano elite "Steinway Artists".
In March 2021, she released her latest album "Elégie" featuring her favorite pieces by Rachmaninov, Schubert, and Bach.

After many years of working on Goldberg Variations of Bach, she created in 2020 a multimedia project "Goldberg Visions" together with French visual artist Isabelle Françaix, combining music and video.
Willing to communicate more with her audience, Irina Lankova launches "Piano Unveiled" in 2016, an informal concert, enriched with her personal comments and destined to various publics.
Since 2015, she is the artistic director of International Music Festival Max van der Linden in Belgium.
Sergei Rachmaninov, Franz Liszt (2004, CD): Rachmaninov Preludes Op.
Alexander Scriabin (2006, CD): Sonates No. 2 & No. 9, Pieces Op.
Frédéric Chopin (2008, CD): Sonata No. 3, Ballade No. 1, Scherzo No. 2, Nocturnes
Franz Schubert (2013, CD Indésens): Drei Klavierstücke D. 946, Piano Sonata D. 959, Impromptu D. 899
"Caprice" (2015, CD Indésens): with violinist Tatiana Samouil
"Goldberg Visions" (2020, CD): Johann Sebastian Bach Goldberg Variations

She is invited to play in many international festivals: Piano Folies Touquet, Académie d'Eté de Nice, Sagra Musicale Umbria, Schiermonnikoog Kamermuziekefestival, Festival de Wallonie, Brussels Summer Festival, Fortissimo d'Orleans, Berlin Summer Festival, etc.
